om":"Askham, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom","Scarborough, Yorkshire, England":"Scarborough, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ughtred","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Outred  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Outred","meanings":["English: (i) relationship name from the Middle English personal name  <i>Utred</i>,  <i>Oughtred</i> (Old English  <i>Ūhtrǣd</i>, a compound of  <i>ūht</i> of unknown meaning +  <i>rǣd</i> ‘advice’). (ii) the name may sometimes have been confused with, or be a phonetic variant of   Outridge  . Compare George Outrid, 1682, with George Outridge, 1685 in   IGI   (Cuckfield, Sussex)."]}]},{"name":"Katherine","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of   Christopher ;  also of   Katherine   and its variants. In the medieval period it was a pet form of   Christian   and   Christiana ."],"variants":[{"name":"Christopher","meanings":["From the Greek name <i>Khristophoros</i>, from <i>Khristos</i> ‘Christ’ + <i>pherein</i> ‘to bear’. This was popular among early Christians, conscious of the fact that they were metaphorically bearing Christ in their hearts. A later, over-literal interpretation of the name gave rise to the legend of a saint who actually bore the Christ-child over a stream; he is regarded as the patron of travellers. In England the name was uncommon in the Middle Ages, but became very popular in the 16th century, especially in parts of the North."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":44,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Katherine Ughtred was born in 1338, in Devon, England, her father, Sir Thomas Ughtred 1st Baron Ughtred, was 47 and her mother, Margaret Burdon, was 43. She married Edmund De Sandford in 1365, in Devon, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1416, in her hometown, at the age of 78."},"et":{"1338–1416":"1338–1416","1329–1401":"1329–1401","1325–1392":"1325–1392","1360–1430":"1360–1430","1366–1400":"1366–1400","1291–1365":"1291–1365","1295–1365":"1295–1365","6 Jun 1366":"6. juuni 1366","1295":"1295","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","12 May 1365":"12. mai 1365","1392":"1392","1291":"1291","1338":"1338","Abt 1360":"umbes 1360","1325":"1325","1401":"1401","1400":"1400","1366":"1366","1365":"1365","29 January 1328":"29. jaanuar 1328","1430":"1430","about 1400":"umbes 1400","1329":"1329","1416":"1416","Devonshire, Devon, England":"Devon, England","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Low Catton, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Low Catton, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Askham, Eden district, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom":"Askham, Westmorland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Scarborough, Yorkshire, England":"Scarborough, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1338–1416":"1338–1416","1329–1401":"1329–1401","1325–1392":"1325–1392","1360–1430":"1360–1430","1366–1400":"1366–1400","1291–1365":"1291–1365","1295–1365":"1295–1365","6 Jun 1366":"6. kesäkuuta 1366","1295":"1295","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","12 May 1365":"12. toukokuuta 1365","1392":"1392","1291":"1291","1338":"1338","Abt 1360":"noin 1360","1325":"1325","1401":"1401","1400":"1400","1366":"1366","1365":"1365","29 January 1328":"29. tammikuuta 1328","1430":"1430","about 1400":"noin 1400","1329":"1329","1416":"1416","Devonshire, Devon, England":"Devon, England","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Low Catton, Yorkshire